The paper proposes a deep neural network for supervised learning on neuroanatomical shapes, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. The network operates on raw point clouds, which suggests a focus on point cloud processing and analysis, a subfield of CV. The end-to-end training stage of the network involves learning an optimal representation, which is a common goal in ML. The proposed network consists of multiple branches, which suggests a focus on multi-task learning, a subfield of ML. Finally, the paper visualizes the important parts of the anatomy for the prediction, which suggests a focus on interpretability and explainability, a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and CL. Based on these observations, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CL.
